2026-05-17 06:37:45 | DEBUG | strands_evaluation.instrumentation.agent_plugins | Model response #12 [role=assistant block=1 tool_use] execute_ideal({"intent": "Load identity theft report counts by metropolitan area for all New England states in 2024, deduplicate by metropolitan area name, and return top 5 by total report count.", "code": "import pandas as pd, re\n\n# New England states\nstates = [\"Connecticut\",\"Maine\",\"Massachusetts\",\"New Hampshire\",\"Rhode Island\",\"Vermont\"]\n\n# Use a single consistent dataset id containing the state MSA identity theft CSVs\nbase = \"s3://sana-kramabench/datagov/kramabench-legal-hard-1/files/csn-data-book-2024-csv/CSVs/State MSA Identity Theft data/\"\n\npaths = {s: base + f\"{s}.csv\" for s in states}\n\n# Read available files; some may 404; fall back to same base under other dataset ids if needed\ncandidates_dataset_ids = [\"kramabench-legal-hard-1\",\"kramabench-legal-hard-15\",\"kramabench-legal-hard-14\",\"kramabench-legal-hard-16\",\"kramabench-legal-hard-2\",\"kramabench-legal-hard-30\"]\n\nrows=[]\nfor dsid in candidates_dataset_ids:\n    for s in states:\n        uri = f\"s3://sana-kramabench/datagov/{dsid}/files/csn-data-book-2024-csv/CSVs/State MSA Identity Theft data/{s}.csv\"\n        try:\n            df = pd.read_csv(uri, skip_blank_lines=True)\n            # Find column names/structure\n            # The file has first column 'Metropolitan Areas: Identity Theft Reports' and second unlabeled column '# of Reports'\n            # Coerce\n            if df.shape[1] < 2:\n                continue\n            col_area = df.columns[0]\n            col_count = df.columns[1]\n            df2 = df[[col_area,col_count]].copy()\n            df2.columns = [\"Metropolitan Area\",\"Reports\"]\n            # Drop header/footer junk rows\n            df2 = df2.dropna(subset=[\"Metropolitan Area\"])\n            df2[\"Metropolitan Area\"] = df2[\"Metropolitan Area\"].astype(str)\n            df2 = df2[~df2[\"Metropolitan